Writing About Mathematics
1. Explain why the sum of a and 4 can be written as a + 4 or as 4 + a.
2. Explain why 3 less than a can be written as a - 3 but not as 3 - a.

3-2 TRANSLATING VERBAL PHRASES INTO SYMBOLS
A knowledge of arithmetic is important in algebra. Since the variables represent
numbers that are familiar to you, it will be helpful to solve each problem by first
using a simpler related problem; that is, relate similar arithmetic problems to the
given algebraic one.
